},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Sometimes it is necessary to limit a live video frame detection or recognition to a certain rectangular area with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a specific aspect ratio: the region or rectangle of interest. This is where a view finder comes in.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It crops the video frame to that region of interest before passing it to any scanner. Usually","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the performance of scanners gain a benefit from it because less pixels must be processed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Additionally, to guide the user, the view finder visualizes the region of interest by drawing a rectangle around","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on the user interface.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotDocumentScannerSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotDocumentScannerSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration"}},"variantOverrides":[{"patch":[{"path":"\/identifier\/interfaceLanguage","op":"replace","value":"occ"},{"path":"\/metadata\/roleHeading","op":"replace","value":"Instance Property"},{"path":"\/metadata\/title","op":"replace","value":"lineWidth"},{"path":"\/metadata\/symbolKind","op":"replace","value":"property"},{"path":"\/metadata\/fragments","op":"replace","value":[{"text":"lineWidth","kind":"identifier"}]},{"path":"\/topicSections","op":"add","value":null},{"path":"\/relationshipsSections","op":"add","value":null},{"path":"\/seeAlsoSections","op":"add","value":null},{"path":"\/primaryContentSections\/0","op":"replace","value":{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@CGFloat","kind":"typeIde